      + Executing the code on hardware platforms implies taking into account external parameters that might influence energy consumption, such as CPU temperature. A cooldown period could mitigate this effect, but again, this complicates the experiment design. The static analysis is not affected by these external hardware parameters, offers results instantly, but at the same time, these given results rely on a machine learning model that abstracts the mathematical reasoning behind the results, while the original methodology provides a more direct, empirical measurement of energy consumption.

